705259f-d.title: Brooklyn: Kings Highway - Avenue H
705259f-d.text:
(1)
Kings Highway, north from Ave. E. At theleft is the Manhattan Beach
DDivision of the Long Island R.R. The Marns etc. at right were John Ditmars.
They were in existence in 1900. The dirt road now Kingshighway, was known as
the Road from Flatlands to New Lots.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(2)
The same, showing only the railroad.
May 1922.

(3)
The same as No. 1.
May 1922.

(4)
The same, looking northeast from Utica Ave.
1922.
